                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/42.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">O’Shaughnessy</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-29T14:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>748. The German Minister complains that a great many German subjects, resident in
                    the territory of Tepic, have suffered a great many depredations from the rebels
                    and that the rebels have stated that they are in connection with Carranza and
                    that he has given orders that as the United States has not recognized Huerta,
                    the property of Americans is to be spared and those of all other nations to be
                    treated without respect. I have informed the German Minister that I would bring
                    this matter to your earnest attention, to the end that Carranza be informed of
                    this state of affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
